{"lemma":"فَرْدٌ","slug":"فَرْدٌ","root":"ف.ر.د","root_slug":"ف-ر-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَرْد","root":"فرد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":9,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":21},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33429","n33430","n33434","n33435"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AF%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be single, be alone"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be singular, be unique"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to withdraw, retire, segregate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spread, spread out, extend, stretch"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to roll out (as dough), unfold"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to individualize, separate into units, make odd or unequal go another, isolate, seclude oneself"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"alone, single"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sole, only"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lonely"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"solitary"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"singular, unique, matchless, unrivaled, unparalleled, nonpareil, peerless, incomparable, nonesuch"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"one and only"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"odd, uneven (number)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one, a single person, individual, somebody, someone"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"soldier, private"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"member (of a group)","examples":[{"text":"هُنَاكَ يَجْلِسُ جَمِيعُ أَفْرَادٍ الْعَائِلَةِ حَوْلَ السُّفْرَةِ.","english":"There are all the family (members) sitting around the dining table."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"singular","tags":["singular"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one, one of a couple, one of a pair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pistol"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَدَ (farada, “to spread, to unfold”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spreading, unfolding"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33429","headword_ar":"فَرَدَ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor"},{"kind":"text","text":", [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwdN","text_ar":"فُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, single; sole;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one, and no more."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  See also 7, (with which two other forms of the unaugmented verb, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farida","text_ar":"فَرِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruda","text_ar":"فَرُدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", are also mentioned,) in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33430","headword_ar":"فرّد","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taforiydN","text_ar":"تَفْرِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He applied himself to the study of practical religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the law, and withdrew from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rest of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mankind, and attended only to the observance of the commands and prohibitions"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, T, L, K.) [See also the part. n., below.]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n33434","headword_ar":"فَرْدَ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Single; sole; only; one, and no more;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"witora","text_ar":"وِتْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, L, Msb;) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [and, used as a subst.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an individual, person"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodapN","text_ar":"فَرْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodaYo","text_ar":"فَرْدَىْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which latter is anomalous, as though fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodaAnu","text_ar":"فَرْدَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAdN","text_ar":"اَفْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAdaY","text_ar":"فُرَادَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"which latter is anomalous, as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furodaAnu","text_ar":"فُرْدَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb) and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodaYo","text_ar":"فَرْدَىْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukaAraY","text_ar":"سُكَارَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukoraAnu","text_ar":"سُكْرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraY","text_ar":"سَكْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAdN","text_ar":"فُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadadotu Ald~araAhima","text_ar":"عَدَدْتُ الدَّرَاهِمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAdAF","text_ar":"اَفْرَاداً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I counted the dirhems one by one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as has no equal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, M, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAdN","text_ar":"اَفْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAdaY","text_ar":"فُرَادَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[respecting which latter see above]. (K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarodu","text_ar":"الفَرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet applied to God means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Single; the Sole; the One;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who has no equal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like; the Unequalled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, L:) but Az says, I have not found it so applied in the Sunneh; and no epithet should be applied to God except such as He has applied to Himself, or such as the Prophet has applied to Him. (L.) And one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofN farodN","text_ar":"سَيْفٌ فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faradN","text_ar":"فَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, L, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furudN","text_ar":"فُرُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faridN","text_ar":"فَرِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farudN","text_ar":"فَرُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariydN","text_ar":"فَرِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodadN","text_ar":"فَرْدَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, but the third and fifth not in the text of the K as given in the TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sword having diversified wavy marks, streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw firinodK","text_ar":"ذُو فِرِنْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", K, [in the TA"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wafirinodN","text_ar":"وَفِرِنْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though one said also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayofN firinodN","text_ar":"سَيْفٌ فِرِنْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is evidently a mistake,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unequalled"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in excellence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"half"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as is alone, by himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart from others; unconnected with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unattended by, others; solitary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mut~aHidN","text_ar":"مُتَّحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kaAna waHodahu","text_ar":"مَا كَانَ وَحْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Lth, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unmixed with others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in which sense it is] a word of more common application than"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2364},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"witorN","text_ar":"وِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and more special than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHidN","text_ar":"وَاحِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kull p. 278:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaAdN","text_ar":"فِرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAdN","text_ar":"اَفْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwdN","text_ar":"فُرُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, as will be shown below]: an ex. of the first of these pls. occurs in the saying, (cited by IAar, L,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taxal~ufa Als~aqori firaAda Als~irobi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As the hawk's seizing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carrying off by force, those that are apart from the others of the flock of birds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, L. See, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAdN","text_ar":"فُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Hence,] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaworN farodN","text_ar":"ثَوْرٌ فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aYo'N farodN","text_ar":"شَىْءٌ فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faridN","text_ar":"فَرِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faradN","text_ar":"فَرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farudN","text_ar":"فَرُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furudN","text_ar":"فُرُدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAridN","text_ar":"فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariydN","text_ar":"فَرِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwdN","text_ar":"فَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodaAnu","text_ar":"فَرْدَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforadN","text_ar":"مُفْرَدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$wh","text_ar":"شوه"},{"kind":"text","text":"),]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bull,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is alone, by itself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart from others; solitary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate from others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidorapN faAridapN","text_ar":"سِدْرَةٌ فَارِدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lote-tree apart from others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajarapN","text_ar":"شَجَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAridN","text_ar":"فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAridapN","text_ar":"فَارِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tree apart from others."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, * TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaboyapN faAridN","text_ar":"ظَبْيَةٌ فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A gazelle apart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate, from the herd."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN faAridN","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miforaAdN","text_ar":"مِفْرَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faruwdN","text_ar":"فَرُودٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel that goes away alone, apart from others, in the pasture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and at the water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in explanation of the last, and L;) the epithet applied to the male being ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAridN","text_ar":"فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", only. (M, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bih`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"بِهٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa faAridN","text_ar":"هُوَ فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is alone in this affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And it is said in a trad., ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAa tuEad~u faAridatukumo","text_ar":"لاَ تُعَدُّ فَارِدَتُكُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Your ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat, that ye have set apart from the flock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herd, that ye may milk her in the tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house, shall not be reckoned"},{"kind":"text","text":"[among those for which ye are to pay the poorrate]: (A:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is over and above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariyDap","text_ar":"فَرِيضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed number of camels, &c., to be given in payment of the poor-rate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall not be added to the latter and reckoned therewith."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And in another it is said, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAa yagul~u faAridatukumo","text_ar":"لاَ يَغُلُّ فَارِدَتُكُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. by Th as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such of you as shall segregate himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as, for instance, one or two,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and gain spoil, shall"},{"kind":"text","text":"resign it to the collective body, and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not act unfaithfully"},{"kind":"text","text":"by taking it for himself. (M, L.) And in another,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faminokumu Almuzodalifu","text_ar":"فَمِنْكُمُ المُزْدَلِفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibu AlEimaAmapi Alfarodapi","text_ar":"صَاحِبُ العِمَامَةِ الفَرْدَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And of you is El-Muzdelif, he of the solitary turban:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this was said of him because, when he rode, no one with him wore a turban, to show honour to him. (L.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiyotuhu","text_ar":"لَقِيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodayoni","text_ar":"فَرْدَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him, we two being alone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAdu Aln~ujuwmi","text_ar":"اَفْرَادُ النُّجُومِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, L, K,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwduhaA","text_ar":"فُرُودُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The brightly-shining stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~araAriYo'u","text_ar":"الدَّرَارِىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the horizon"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when other stars, there, are invisible"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: so called because they are apart from the other [visible] stars. (M, L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfuruwdu","text_ar":"الفُرُودُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, L, and so in some copies of the K,) in some copies of the K ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfuroduwdu","text_ar":"الفُرْدُودُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and thus in the CK,] but the former is the right, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain stars, disposed in a row, behind the Pleiades;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around the Pleiades:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain bright stars around the Pleiades."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L.) And (L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain stars around"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDaAri","text_ar":"حَضَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], which is one of the two stars called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuHolifaAni","text_ar":"المُحْلِفَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L, TA,) the other whereof is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwazonu","text_ar":"الوَزْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain small stars with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaDaAri","text_ar":"حَضَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so called because situate apart from the latter, by its side. (Kitáb Anwá el- 'Arab, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarodu","text_ar":"الفَرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the hinder part of the neck of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ujaAE","text_ar":"الشُّجَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the constellation"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hydra;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which star is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eunuqu","text_ar":"عُنُقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ujaAEi","text_ar":"الشُّجَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kzw in his description of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$jAE","text_ar":"الشجاع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farodN","text_ar":"فَرْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One side of a jaw:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAdN","text_ar":"اَفْرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, L.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sandal such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"simoTN","text_ar":"سِمْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not patched, nor having a second sole added to it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sandal having a single sole; not having a sole composed of two pieces of leather sewed together, one beneath the other;"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus in the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA xayora mano yamo$iY binaElK farodi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O best of such as walk with a single-soled sandal"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning O best of the great men of the Arabs; for sandals were worn by the Arabs, exclusively of the foreigners; and thin sandals, only by the kings and chief persons of the former. (L.) ―         -b9-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAridN","text_ar":"فَارِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bull"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wild bull"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Lth, T, L. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muforadN","text_ar":"مُفْرَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b10-  [The pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aforaAdu","text_ar":"الاَفْرَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a conventional term in lexicology signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What have been transmitted by only one of the lexicologists;"},{"kind":"text","text":"what is thus transmitted, if the transmitter is a person of exactness (as Aboo-Zeyd and ElKhaleel and others), is admitted. (Mz, 5th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":". [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=HaAdu","text_ar":"الا=حَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHadN","text_ar":"اَحَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; a similar, but less restricted, term: and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmafaAriydu","text_ar":"المَفَارِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","L","Lth","M","K","T","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n33435","headword_ar":"فَرَدٌ","root":"frd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faridN","text_ar":"فَرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farudN","text_ar":"فَرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furudN","text_ar":"فُرُدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, first quarter: and again, in the second quarter: and for the first and second and third, see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furaAdN","text_ar":"فُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}